Advanced atrioventricular block associated with atrial tachycardia caused by Mycoplasma pneumoniae infection. Atrial tachycardia with atrioventricular (AV) block has been recognized as a common manifestation of digitalis toxicity. We describe here an unusual case of transient advanced AV block associated with atrial tachycardia in a 6 year old boy with evidence of Mycoplasma pneumoniae infection.